FBIS3-55511 "drsov006_a_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Government Agrees To Unfreeze Credit to Armenia LD0801100194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0700 GMT 8 Jan 94 LD0801100194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Agreement on Russia's unfreezing last year's credit to Armenia, amounting to 24,000 million rubles [R], has been reached at a meeting between the two countries' prime ministers, Viktor Chernomyrdin and Grant Bagratyan. According to the SNARK agency, Moscow will also grant Yerevan credit totaling R10,000 million for rehabilitation work in the earthquake area. Additionally, the sides decided during the talks to consider, before 20 January, the question of the joint running of the Armenian nuclear power station.
